What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Contract Packaging Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Contract Packaging Market

Contract packaging market will reach an estimated valuation of USD 116.93 million by 2028, while registering this growth at a rate of 10.10% for the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Contract packaging market report analyses the growth, which is currently being growing due to the increasing consumer awareness about environmental concerns.

The method of assembling a product or good into its final finished packaging is contract packaging. Depending on the product, the final packaging constitutes a range of types, such as thermoformed/ plastic clamshell or blister packaging, a plastic container, a standing corrugated retail point-of-sale display, or a transport tray. Contract packagers are often charged with something as basic as attaching a bar code sticker to a product or as complicated as the whole package is prepared, built, assembled and fulfilled.

Increasing demand from the e-commerce industry, rising need for latest technology and innovative packaging, growing number of population across the globe, rapid urbanization has led to the demand for packed and ready-to-eat food, high growth in the alcoholic and non-alcoholic beverage industry which employs closures, caps, bottles, cans, and the pouch, services are provided in various shapes and sizes for both liquid and rigid products are some of the major as well as vital factors which will likely to augment the growth of the contract packaging market in the projected timeframe of 2021-2028. On the other hand, improvements in medical sciences and additions to medicines already available for numerous diseases and deficiencies along with motivating more manufacturers to prefer contract package over in-house packaging activities which will further contribute by generating massive opportunities that will lead to the growth of the contract packaging market in the above mentioned projected timeframe.

Increasing levels of competition from in-house packaging along with stringent government regulations which will likely to act as market restraints factor for the growth of the contract packaging in the projected timeframe mentioned above. Volatility in the prices of raw material along with wide gap between demand and supply which will become the biggest and foremost challenge for the growth of the market.

